commit.message: Removed Mac packages as I can no longer test them
Verbose output during debugging

Single Pole/Zero bugfix

This fixes a bug reported already in the original DSPFilters:
https://github.com/vinniefalco/DSPFilters/issues/29 and
confirmed for the JAVA port https://github.com/berndporr/iirj/issues/27.
That's now fixed.
Added safeguards that it's the normalised frequency for response().
Better labelling
Added comparison between impulse response and analytical calc from poles/zeros
Updated the online docs
Added new options

Bugfix so that complex template types are exported to DLL.

Under Windows the complex template types are not automatically
exported to the DLL so that one could not get the frequency
response or the pole/zero pairs. That's now fixed.
Rand seems to be the one which is more cross platform!

rbj_update.cpp needs random() which is in stdlib

@c-buzz reported a compile failur because random()
wasn't defined. stdlib wasn't included so I added
that.
Removed unnceccary functions which are no longer used.

Bumped up cmake version, added c+11 per lib and pruned warnings.

See: https://github.com/berndporr/iir1/pull/50

Worked in CMake: add IIR1_BUILD_DEMO option & consistent naming #49

- rename `INSTALL_STATIC` to `IIR1_INSTALL_STATIC`
- allow `IIR1_BUILD_TESTING OFF` to disable tests even when iir1 is top project
- add `IIR1_BUILD_DEMO` to allow to disable build of demo executables

Thanks, @SpaceIm

commit.message:
`__declspec(dllexport)` at build time of shared lib only

- `__declspec(dllexport)` should not be defined at consume time of shared lib (it's nothing or `__declspec(dllimport)` eventually)
- for static lib, no there should not be any `__declspec(dllexport)` at build or consume time
- `iir_EXPORTS` is automatically injected as a private definition by CMake when `irr` target is shared
add option IIR1_NO_EXCEPTIONS

remove useless include_directories in demo & test

include dirs are already propagated through target_link_libraries to iir_static

remove useless enforcements of CMake policies

CMP0048 & CMP0042 are already NEW as per current cmake_minimum_required to 3.1
Merge branch 'SpaceIm-fix/dllexport'

Reverted changes which added the visibility attributes.

Thanks @SpaceIm for the PR. However, these are two in one.
The one is the macro which we agree that this should be
made IIR-specific and also that templates cannot be exported
so thank you very much. Well spotted!

Regarding linker attributes:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52719364/how-to-use-the-attribute-visibilitydefault
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/71284410/what-exactly-setcmake-cxx-visibility-preset-hidden-does-with-cmake

attributes are really just meant to fix things
very close to the compilter/hardware such as packed structs
but they are not a general purpose language element.

So, sorry but that's not merged.

properly export symbols in shared lib

- rename DllExport to IIR_EXPORT, since the former is a too generic name
- always define IIR_EXPORT to empty in static lib
- hide all symbols regardless of os/compiler
- do not export templates, they can't be exported by definition
